00:15:44.560 --> 00:15:51.800
Well, because everything in ministry that they have done for three and a half years

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:55.720
has been in the presence of the Lord Jesus.

00:15:56.040 --> 00:15:59.880
Hey, if they moved, if He moved, they moved.

00:15:59.880 --> 00:16:02.920
They were with Him when He did great miracles.

00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:04.400
They've seen Him heal.

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:06.560
They've seen Him raise dead people.

00:16:06.560 --> 00:16:08.840
They've seen Him turn water to wine.

00:16:08.840 --> 00:16:11.400
They have seen miracle after miracle.

00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:17.640
And as long as He is standing by their side, they're good.

00:16:17.640 --> 00:16:20.680
But now He's going.

00:16:20.680 --> 00:16:24.120
And can we really do this?

00:16:24.120 --> 00:16:27.680
Can we really do what He's asking us to do?

00:16:27.680 --> 00:16:28.680
If He's not here?

00:16:28.680 --> 00:16:31.400
I don't know about you.

00:16:31.400 --> 00:16:36.960
I sometimes try to appear to be confident, but when God has told me to do something and

00:16:36.960 --> 00:16:43.920
I say, yeah, I'm going to do it, and I turn the light out, I say, why did I say that?

00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:48.400
And God makes them a promise.

00:16:48.400 --> 00:16:52.720
I will be present with you.

00:16:53.600 --> 00:17:02.240
I said to you the other evening that one of the greatest forces that discourages and brings

00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:08.080
young missionaries home from the field is a sense of loneliness and isolation.

00:17:08.080 --> 00:17:10.320
I'm here by myself.

00:17:10.320 --> 00:17:11.640
Does anybody know I'm here?

00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:13.760
Does anybody care about what we're doing?

00:17:13.760 --> 00:17:15.880
Does anybody care about our struggle?

00:17:15.880 --> 00:17:18.200
Does anybody know we have a crisis?

00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.280
Does anybody know we have a need?

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:23.960
Does anybody even know we're here?

00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:26.520
I haven't experienced it to that level.

00:17:26.520 --> 00:17:32.920
But when we started Heritage Baptist Church in 1981, oh man, it was great.

00:17:32.920 --> 00:17:38.640
Because for the first three weeks, group after group came from Pittsburgh from our church

00:17:38.640 --> 00:17:39.680
there and helped us.

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:41.320
We knocked doors together.

00:17:41.320 --> 00:17:43.980
We were leading people to Christ at the door.

00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:47.520
We were announcing time for the prayer meeting and the first service.

00:17:47.520 --> 00:17:48.960
It was great.

00:17:48.960 --> 00:17:49.960
But you know what happened?

00:17:50.640 --> 00:17:53.440
They couldn't keep coming from Pittsburgh.

00:17:53.440 --> 00:17:58.740
And so more and more my mother and father would come from Kentucky and they would stay

00:17:58.740 --> 00:18:03.760
and watch the kids and Nancy and I would go out soul winning, but mother and dad couldn't

00:18:03.760 --> 00:18:06.040
keep coming.

00:18:06.040 --> 00:18:10.920
I'll never forget those days when mother and dad couldn't keep coming and we had three

00:18:10.920 --> 00:18:15.120
children and Nancy had to stay home and care for the children.

00:18:15.120 --> 00:18:18.680
And I don't know if you know this, but when you are starting a church and you have no

00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:22.320
congregation, you ain't got a lot to do.

00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:23.720
And so you go soul winning.

00:18:23.720 --> 00:18:25.840
You say, you said ain't preacher.

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:28.720
It's good preaching, isn't it?

00:18:28.720 --> 00:18:33.239
You go soul winning and you go soul winning by yourself.

00:18:33.239 --> 00:18:39.200
Going soul winning by yourself on an August afternoon when it's 184 degrees and the humidity

00:18:39.200 --> 00:18:45.880
is 362 is not an easy thing.

00:18:45.880 --> 00:18:53.559
I can remember going up to a door and just being so rudely treated by a lady.

00:18:53.559 --> 00:18:58.880
I mean, it was just so ugly the way she talked and get off my property and don't bring that

00:18:58.880 --> 00:19:00.679
stuff around here.

00:19:00.679 --> 00:19:06.160
And boy, when I'm walking back down to the main sidewalk, I'm thinking to myself, nobody

00:19:06.160 --> 00:19:08.360
knows the trouble.

00:19:08.360 --> 00:19:10.760
I mean, I'm feeling sorry for myself.

00:19:10.760 --> 00:19:16.880
And I am thinking to myself, what am I doing out here?

00:19:16.880 --> 00:19:19.360
These people are not, what am I doing out here?

00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:21.160
I'm all by myself.

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:28.480
You ever have one of those moments where the Holy Spirit just gets you and he just stops

00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:30.280
you.

00:19:30.280 --> 00:19:34.520
And I'm telling you, I don't know if you've ever been to Dale City, but in the middle

00:19:34.520 --> 00:19:40.840
of Dale City on a sidewalk on a, I think it was a Friday afternoon in August.

00:19:40.840 --> 00:19:49.280
I'm sweating like a pig and I had an epiphany and the Holy Spirit stopped me and he said,

00:19:49.280 --> 00:19:53.000
you have not gone to one door by yourself.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:57.119
You have not written one sermon by yourself.

00:19:57.119 --> 00:19:59.440
You have not talked to one or.

00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.800
counsel to anybody by yourself. You are not here by

00:20:02.800 --> 00:20:09.240
yourself. I am present with you every step of this way.

00:20:09.240 --> 00:20:12.680
And I say this to you, young man, young woman, young

00:20:12.680 --> 00:20:17.720
couple, I say to you that God does not abandon you when

00:20:17.720 --> 00:20:22.920
you answer His call. God goes with you. And the promise

00:20:22.920 --> 00:20:26.460
that He makes to you is whether it is a sidewalk in

00:20:26.460 --> 00:20:31.060
Glendale City or a dirt path or a jungle in Africa or

00:20:31.060 --> 00:20:35.300
Burma, I know exactly where that jungle is, God says. I

00:20:35.300 --> 00:20:38.000
know the way in, I know the way out, I know what I've

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:41.540
got you there for, I know how to care for you. I will

00:20:41.540 --> 00:20:46.380
be with you. Here's number two. Turn with me quickly to

00:20:46.380 --> 00:20:53.820
Mark chapter 16. Not only does He promise us His

00:20:53.820 --> 00:20:59.720
presence, He promises us protection. Look at verse 15.

00:20:59.720 --> 00:21:06.100
And He said unto them, Go ye into all the world, and

00:21:06.100 --> 00:21:08.660
preach the gospel to every creature. That's the part of

00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:11.700
the commission we know. He that believeth and is

00:21:11.700 --> 00:21:15.300
baptized shall be saved, but he that believeth not shall

00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:18.600
be damned. And these signs shall follow them that

00:21:18.600 --> 00:21:23.040
believe. In my name shall they cast out devils. They

00:21:23.060 --> 00:21:25.639
shall speak with new tongues. They shall take up

00:21:25.639 --> 00:21:29.139
serpents. And if they drink any deadly thing, it shall

00:21:29.139 --> 00:21:32.880
not hurt them. They shall lay hands on the sick, and they

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:35.840
shall recover. Now can I tell you something? Right now

00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:40.779
your pastor is nervous. I want to assure you my

00:21:40.779 --> 00:21:43.959
theology is correct, my dispensationalism is correct.

00:21:43.959 --> 00:21:48.620
I know what these verses say. There was a time in the New

00:21:48.620 --> 00:21:53.319
Testament when God used signed gifts through the

00:21:53.319 --> 00:21:58.260
apostles. They had signed gifts because the gift would

00:21:58.260 --> 00:22:01.160
confirm that they were speaking for God and that the

00:22:01.160 --> 00:22:04.319
message they were delivering was from the Lord. We don't

00:22:04.319 --> 00:22:07.800
need signed gifts anymore because we have the completed

00:22:07.800 --> 00:22:12.600
Word of God. We have it in its totality. Here's the Word.

00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:17.380
But what I am suggesting to you is that we serve a

00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:24.279
supernatural God. We serve a God who is not bound by

00:22:24.279 --> 00:22:29.520
natural law. He is the author of natural law. And by the

00:22:29.520 --> 00:22:33.880
way, there is no mother nature, but there is a Creator

00:22:33.880 --> 00:22:39.919
God. And God is able to suspend natural law, transcend

00:22:39.919 --> 00:22:45.660
natural law. God is able to protect His people wherever

00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:50.619
they are on God's created earth. Now I'm not saying

00:22:50.619 --> 00:22:54.520
difficult and bad things never happen to good people. What

00:22:54.520 --> 00:22:58.360
I am saying is that accidents don't happen to good people

00:22:58.360 --> 00:23:02.339
that are serving the Lord. And if God does allow a

00:23:02.339 --> 00:23:04.839
difficult thing into your life, it is accompanied with

00:23:04.839 --> 00:23:10.479
His great grace. I am saying to you that as I view things

00:23:10.540 --> 00:23:15.600
today, I see more and more people fearful of stepping

00:23:15.600 --> 00:23:20.839
into a call to a mission field. I even observe parents

00:23:20.839 --> 00:23:26.320
who are fearful of allowing their children to even

00:23:26.320 --> 00:23:30.160
entertain a call to a mission field. And I would suggest to

00:23:30.160 --> 00:23:34.619
you tonight that your child is safer in a mud hut in the

00:23:34.619 --> 00:23:38.760
midst of Africa eating monkey meat than they are in a

00:23:38.779 --> 00:23:42.680
comfortable suburb out of the will of God close to you so

00:23:42.680 --> 00:23:46.820
you can have your grandchildren there. We have got to think

00:23:46.820 --> 00:23:51.320
right on this thing. Listen, the Apostle Paul was a man

00:23:51.320 --> 00:23:55.160
surrendered to the Lord. And I know he was an apostle, and I

00:23:55.160 --> 00:23:58.800
know you can discount it. But I'm just telling you that he

00:23:58.800 --> 00:24:03.940
has been in the water more than any apostle I know. He

00:24:03.940 --> 00:24:08.639
was shipwrecked. And I don't think he went to the YMCA and

00:24:08.720 --> 00:24:12.960
took swim lessons as a teen, alright? I think God protected

00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:16.299
him. I think God brought a piece of wood by at the right

00:24:16.299 --> 00:24:19.500
time so that he could hang on to that wood and get to the

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:23.140
shore. I think when he got to the shore he was cold, and God

00:24:23.140 --> 00:24:26.440
said, start a fire. And he went and got wood. And when he

00:24:26.440 --> 00:24:29.380
brought his hand out from that wood there was a serpent

00:24:29.380 --> 00:24:32.480
attached to his hand. That would have done it for me, I

00:24:32.480 --> 00:24:38.360
guarantee you. He shook it off. And God was able to stop

00:24:38.580 --> 00:24:41.380
the venom. I don't know whether God stopped the snake

00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:45.820
from envenomating him, or whether God stopped the venom.

00:24:45.820 --> 00:24:48.279
I don't know what God did. God can do what He wants to do

00:24:48.279 --> 00:24:53.320
because God is able. One of my favorite missionary

00:24:53.320 --> 00:24:57.260
biographies is a book called, Evidence Not Seen, Darlene

00:24:57.260 --> 00:25:01.899
Diebler-Rose. And Darlene Diebler-Rose and her first

00:25:01.899 --> 00:25:05.899
husband were on Papua New Guinea at the outbreak of World

00:25:05.940 --> 00:25:11.279
War II. And they were taken captive by the Japanese. Mr.

00:25:11.279 --> 00:25:16.880
Rose, or Mr. Diebler, was put into a separate camp from

00:25:16.880 --> 00:25:20.320
Darlene, and he passed away in that labor camp. Darlene

00:25:20.320 --> 00:25:24.320
survived the war. One of the things that she had secreted

00:25:24.320 --> 00:25:28.299
away was just a little New Testament. It was the most

00:25:28.299 --> 00:25:32.140
precious possession she had. And the Japanese were cruel,

00:25:32.179 --> 00:25:35.380
hard, hard masters. And they wanted to protect their

00:25:35.380 --> 00:25:38.880
workers. And so as the war went on, as the American

00:25:38.880 --> 00:25:42.619
bombers came over, they weren't always able to discern,

00:25:42.619 --> 00:25:46.459
is this an American barracks, or is this a Japanese barracks?

00:25:46.459 --> 00:25:50.299
And so often the labor camp would be bombed

00:25:50.299 --> 00:25:53.799
indiscriminately. And the Japanese, not wanting to lose

00:25:53.799 --> 00:25:57.339
their laborers, insisted that you leave the barracks and go

00:25:57.339 --> 00:26:00.480
out into the ditch where there was some protection from the

00:26:00.540 --> 00:26:04.720
bombs. And one day the air raid siren sounded, and Ms. Rose

00:26:04.720 --> 00:26:09.119
ran from the barracks and into the ditch, the protected area,

00:26:09.119 --> 00:26:13.619
and it dawned on her she forgot her New Testament. And it

00:26:13.619 --> 00:26:16.799
just killed her to think that New Testament might get blown

00:26:16.799 --> 00:26:20.299
up, burned up. She got up out of the ditch and ran back in

00:26:20.299 --> 00:26:23.339
knowing she might get beat for it. But she went back into

00:26:23.339 --> 00:26:26.380
the barracks and got that New Testament. As she came out of

00:26:26.380 --> 00:26:29.739
the door running back to where she was supposed to be, it was

00:26:30.399 --> 00:26:34.779
nothing but a smoking crater where a bomb had hit. You say,

00:26:34.779 --> 00:26:45.119
preacher, what a coincidence. What a God. We don't have to

00:26:45.119 --> 00:26:51.220
live fearfully. We can trust God. He goes out of His way to

00:26:51.220 --> 00:26:58.260
say to us, I am able to protect you if I call you to the field.

00:26:58.320 --> 00:27:08.760
Turn with me quickly, Luke chapter 24. Look at verse 46.

00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:15.200
And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, He said, Father,

00:27:15.200 --> 00:27:23.179
I'm not there in the right place am I? 24. All right, now

00:27:23.179 --> 00:27:27.179
46 will make better sense. He said, and thus it is written,

00:27:27.179 --> 00:27:30.480
and thus it behooved Christ to suffer and to rise from the

00:27:30.480 --> 00:27:34.480
dead the third day. And that repentance and remission of

00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:38.980
sins should be preached in His name among all nations,

00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:43.860
beginning at Jerusalem. And ye are witnesses of these things.

00:27:43.860 --> 00:27:48.820
And behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you. But

00:27:48.820 --> 00:27:52.660
tarry ye in the city of Jerusalem until ye be endued

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:57.519
with power from on high. That's Luke's version of the Great

00:27:57.519 --> 00:28:02.260
Commission. And what Luke says is, listen, I want you to

00:28:02.260 --> 00:28:09.600
preach the gospel and I'm going to endue you with power. Right

00:28:09.600 --> 00:28:13.600
away when we hear that word power, our thought kind of goes

00:28:13.600 --> 00:28:18.580
to, you know, great strength, great muscular strength. But

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:24.299
that's not what God is saying here. Understand this, that

00:28:24.299 --> 00:28:32.080
when we get saved, God gifts us. God gives us a gift that

00:28:32.080 --> 00:28:36.820
enables us to serve Him. And you may be sitting in this room

00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:41.159
tonight with the gift that is necessary for God to use you on

00:28:41.159 --> 00:28:45.859
the field. All the time I run into people who say things

00:28:45.880 --> 00:28:51.820
like, well I could never do that. Did you know that that's

00:28:51.820 --> 00:28:58.059
qualifying you to go to the mission field? God's not really

00:28:58.059 --> 00:29:01.320
all that interested in the ones who are convinced that they're

00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:04.460
the gift of the world and they can do it all. As a matter of

00:29:04.460 --> 00:29:08.940
fact, God has to kind of break them to make them understand

00:29:08.940 --> 00:29:15.960
that without Him they can do nothing. God has already put a

00:29:15.960 --> 00:29:20.200
gift in you. How does it work out here? Hey listen, they are

00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:24.599
to tarry in the upper room and they are to tarry there until

00:29:24.599 --> 00:29:29.179
God in this sign gift way endues them with that giftedness.

00:29:29.179 --> 00:29:33.080
Remember what the giftedness was? It was the ability to

00:29:33.080 --> 00:29:37.880
speak or to be heard in the language of literally hundreds

00:29:37.919 --> 00:29:41.220
of thousands of people, maybe millions in the city of

00:29:41.220 --> 00:29:44.820
Jerusalem on the day of Pentecost. Now you do remember

00:29:44.820 --> 00:29:50.340
that Peter had gone to linguistic school. And you do

00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:54.280
remember that John, he was a professor of languages at

00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:59.039
Galilee University. No he wasn't. Peter was better at

00:29:59.039 --> 00:29:59.539
customizing than John.

00:29:59.539 --> 00:30:01.499
than that he was at preaching, okay?

00:30:02.539 --> 00:30:04.419
You say, preacher, what is your point?

00:30:04.419 --> 00:30:07.979
My point is this, that those men

00:30:07.979 --> 00:30:11.739
did not experience the blessing of Pentecost

00:30:11.739 --> 00:30:16.099
because they had been dutifully prepared in their education.

00:30:16.099 --> 00:30:18.939
They enjoyed the blessing of Pentecost

00:30:18.939 --> 00:30:22.659
because God made them able, because God gifted them.

00:30:22.659 --> 00:30:25.179
And what God is saying is this,

00:30:25.179 --> 00:30:28.779
I promise you, if I call you to the field,

00:30:28.819 --> 00:30:32.899
I will have gifted you what is necessary

00:30:32.899 --> 00:30:35.619
to do what I've called you to do.

